  "doc_id": "39522",
  "text": "TO THE EDITOR: Irritable bowel syndrome (IBS) remains to be a challenge for the gastroenterologist, due to its high prevalence and impacts on poor quality of life (QOL) with unsatisfactory pharmacological treatments. Most of the current treatment modalities for IBS have been directed at symptom relief rather than pathophysiology of the condition, which is heterogenous and poorly understood. [CITATION_1] I read the recent articles by Kim et al. [CITATION_2] about the tegaserod effects on IBS with great interest. The efficacy and safety of tegaserod have been demonstrated by several large randomized controlled trials. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] However, tegaserod was taken off the market by a high chance of having a myocardial infarction, stroke or angina.",
